0. Inspiration of suggestion.

This is the highest kind, and exists when God speaks directly to the mind, communicating what it could not otherwise know, dictating every word, making the human author a mere auditor or secretary of the divine. The Apocalypse and some other parts of the New Testament were written under this influence.¹
